# Cloudflare Pages — URL rewrites and redirects.
# Reference: https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# Single rule for now: SPA fallback. Compose Multiplatform's
# in-memory routing doesn't push URL changes today, so any deep link
# (or refresh on a non-root path) needs to land on `index.html` and
# let the in-app router decide what to render. CF Pages parses this
# top-down and `/* /index.html 200` is the catch-all.
#
# Status code 200 (not 301/302) so the URL stays untouched in the
# address bar and the browser doesn't see a redirect — important if
# we ever wire deep-link handling that reads `window.location` from
# the Kotlin side.
/*    /index.html   200
